# PhD/Master's Research Proposal

## Structure (9 sections)
1. Title & Abstract (~200w)
2. Introduction (~500w)
3. Related Work (~800w)
4. Research Questions (~200w)
5. Methodology (~1000w) ← most important
6. Preliminary Results (~500w, if any)
7. Timeline & Milestones
8. Expected Contributions (~300w)
9. References

## Key Rules
- Methodology: define paradigm, system design, protocol, reproducibility plan
- Timeline: 2-year Master's = defense at Month 22-23 (use milestone-tracker)
- Related Work: by taxonomy, not chronology

## Committee Checklist
- Problem in 1-2 sentences
- Gap supported by ≥3 recent papers
- RQ specific + measurable
- Baselines state-of-the-art
- Timeline padded 20%
